						<summary>

						<p>Kūrattaḷvār shrine, Tiers of the west wall.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1480, Piṅgala, Āśvīja ba. 10, Sunday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1557 A.D., October 17.</hi> The Śaka year quoted is current.</p>						

						<p>Records a gift of land by Ēkāṅgi Naraśiṅgayya, a devotee of Bhaṭṭar (successor of Rāmānuja), for the feeding of the Śrī Vaishṇavas. Published; <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XXIV, No. 480.</p>						

